description:
Double Trouble!

Meet PRIMAVERA BOBINSKI — just one of many adolescent females that a VIRAL-NANOTECH plague is turning into cyber-dolls, or DEAD GIRLS.

Meet IGGY ZWAKH — a DOLL-ADDICT, strung out on the narcotic, vampire-like kisses by which PRIMAVERA and her kind infect human males and replicate themselves.

Together, these two wild, teenage runaways are set to cut a bloody swathe through the mid-21st century, from London to Bangkok, forever seeking out some place where love survives and a boy and his doll might be together.
name: Born to Run

description:
Boy meets girl.

Girl bites boy.

Boy becomes carrier of the DOLL-PLAGUE …

Persecuted, and condemned to languish and die in concentration camps euphemistically called DOLL HOSPITALS, girls born with the NANO-VIRUS that turns them into DOLLS flee their homes and families, knowing that the stage is being set for GENOCIDE.

Iggy and Primavera are on the run …
name: Little Miss Strange

description:
'God,' said Einstein, 'does not play dice with the universe.'

But Einstein had not heard of PRIMAVERA BOBINSKI!

In London, she was metamorphosing. A nano-virus was rewriting her DNA. One year later, in Bangkok, she's a teenage killing machine with a quantum computer for a mind.
name: Helter Skelter

description:
Now in DC’s acclaimed deluxe format, this new hardcover collects all things Death, including DEATH: THE HIGH COST OF LIVING #1-3, DEATH: THE TIME OF YOUR LIFE #1-3, plus extras including “Death Talks about Life” AIDS pamphlet, stories from VERTIGO: WINTER’S EDGE #2 and THE SANDMAN: ENDLESS NIGHTS, the short story “The Wheel” from the 9-11 tribute book, SANDMAN #8 and #20, and art from the DEATH GALLERY!

Back Blurb

You'll See Her Again

A touchstone for a generation of comics readers, Death of the Endless rose from New York Time best-selling author Neil Gaiman's acclaimed masterpiece THE SANDMAN to become one of his most beloved creations. Now, all of Gaiman's tales starring Dream's older sister are gathered here in a definitive hardcover collection.

DEATH: THE DELUXE EDITION EDITION includes the miniseries DEATH: THE HIGH COST OF LIVING and DEATH: THE TIME OF YOUR LIFE together with THE SANDMAN issues "The Sound of Her Wings" and "Facade", the "Death and Venice" chapter from THE SANDMAN: ENDLESS NIGHTS, and the short stories "A Winter's Tale", "The Wheel" and "Death Talks About Life".

This comprehensive volume also features an introspective introduction by musician Tori Amos and an extensive gallery of Death portraits from a host of comics' greatest artists.
name: HC

description:
This volume contains the Atomic City Tales from:

Contains an introduction by Mike Mignola

volume.name: Go Power!: The Complete Atomic City Tales Collection

description:
For centuries, vampire Andrew Bennett kept mankind safe from the supernatural world thanks to a truce he made with his ex-lover Mary, the Queen of Blood. But that truce has reached a bloody end, and Andrew must stop Mary and her forces from going on a killing spree!

Collecting I, VAMPIRE #1-6!

Back Blurb

THE WAR OF THE VAMPIRES BEINGS

For hundreds of years, vampire Andrew Bennett kept mankind safe from the horrors of the supernatural world, thanks to a truce he made his ex-lover Mary, the Queen of Blood. But now the truce has reached a bloody end and Andrew must do everything in his power to stop Mary and her dark forces from wreaking havoc on an unwitting human populace.

Soon enough, across the country, bodies litter the streets as the fiending vampiresse builds her army. A weakened Andrew must seek the aid of unusual allies --- John Constantine, Hellblazer, as well as The Dark Knight himself --- to take down the bloodthirsty Mary. But can he really trust them...and does he truly believe he has the power to stop the Queen of Blood?

I, VAMPIRE: TAINTED LOVE, collecting issues #1-6, features the arresting art of ANDREA SORRENTINO (God of War) and the riveting words of JOSHUA HALE FIALKOV (Echoes).
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Dennis the Menace and the Bible Kids

description:
The first collection of the DC COMICS - THE NEW 52 series!

Who is Voodoo? Is she hero, villain - or both? Learn the truth about Priscilla Kitaen as she leaves a trail of violence across America.

Collects VOODOO #1-6!
name: Volume 1

description: When Holly Holiday gets herself caught by the evil Anti-Claus, it's up to Santa's li'l elfin granddaughter CHRISSIE CLAUS to travel to the K'un-L'un mountains in China to stage a rescue! Also in this issue, when Chrissie travels "Into the Black Forest" on a mission to get magic wood for Santa's workshop, she runs into big trouble she didn't expect.

It's the showdown between Santa's li'l eflin granddaughter CHRISSIE CLAUS and the evil Anti-Claus, featuring a special guest appearance by Sigma-Chi, Master of Claus Fu. Also in this issue, comics' shining goddess of light, FLARE, tells "The Christmas Story."

It's a Champions Christmas special, with a surprise visit from Santa's li'l elfin granddaughter, CHRISSIE CLAUS!

And what a surprise it is! Because when it's time for Icestar and Icicle to make the Champions' annual visit to the Children's Hospital, it's Icicle who channels Chrissie! And the story Chrissie tells once they get there has a few surprises in it for Icestar, too! This classic Christmas treat is by Dennis Mallonee and Lou Manna.
